id: pm-45mb
title: "GH-534: no-op update reports phantom changed_fields in --json while TOON reports empty, and changed_field_count is always null in JSON"
description: "A no-op pm update (field set to its current value) emits changed_fields:['title'] in --json but an empty changed_fields in TOON — the two formats disagree about whether anything changed; agents keying off JSON see phantom mutations. Additionally changed_field_count is computed for TOON but left null in the JSON envelope. Fix: compute changed_fields once from the actual before/after diff and share it across both renderers (uniform output contract — pm-srns territory), and populate changed_field_count as a number (0 for no-op). Check update-many/close envelopes for the same divergence at fix time."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,gh-issue,json-output
created_at: "2026-07-13T08:58:01.446Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T15:33:38.099Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-13T15:32:42.756Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "No-op update reports empty changed_fields in BOTH json and toon; changed_field_count numeric in JSON (0 no-op, N real); update-many/close checked for the same divergence; regression tests; GH-534 closed"
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Resolved by filtering attempted mutations through the persisted before/after document and suppressing no-op writes.
expected_result: No-op updates report no changed fields or history mutation in every output projection.
actual_result: Same-value title updates report changed_field_count=0; real mutations retain precise changed fields and full tests passed.
