  "2026-07-13T14:32:09.854Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"Implementation start: active in the broad SDK/CLI/MCP contract-integrity PR. Live all-status duplicate checks, full item metadata, related closed lineage, GitHub issues/PRs/checks/releases, dependency updates, and security alert surfaces were reviewed before claim. This item shares validation primitives, public SDK semantics, CLI/MCP contracts, and one end-to-end verification surface with pm-chyh, pm-p9sc, pm-45mb, pm-7je0, pm-jh9t, pm-kj4k, pm-hno5, and pm-96vo."
  "2026-07-13T15:32:35.414Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"Evidence: update changed_fields is filtered against the persisted before/after metadata and body, and skipNoop prevents phantom history/write timestamps. JSON reports changed_field_count=0 for a same-title update. update-many and close envelope ownership were evaluated and documented. Focused and full coverage gates passed."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T15:28:07.544Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"update-many already computes row status from actual per-item mutation results, and close is a lifecycle transition rather than a same-value scalar update. The phantom field defect was isolated to update's pre-diff changed_fields accumulation."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T15:28:09.546Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"Mutation output should derive changed_fields from the persisted before/after document, not from attempted assignments, so JSON, TOON, history, and no-op write suppression share one truth."
